{"comments":"Easing — Compound type unifying all easing function varieties.\n\n## Easing Function Types\n\nAn easing function maps normalized time [0,1] to normalized progress [0,1].\nDifferent types of easing serve different purposes:\n\n- **Linear**: Constant velocity, no acceleration\n- **CubicBezier**: Smooth acceleration curves (CSS standard)\n- **Steps**: Discrete jumps (sprite animation, typewriter)\n- **Spring**: Physics-based (natural, responsive feel)\n\n## Usage\n\nThe Easing type allows any animation system to accept any easing approach,\nproviding a unified interface for the runtime to interpret.\n","declarations":[{"children":[{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[112,11],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Temporal/Easing.purs","start":[112,3]},"title":"Linear"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Temporal","CubicBezierEasing"],"CubicBezierEasing"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[113,16],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Temporal/Easing.purs","start":[113,3]},"title":"CubicBezier"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Temporal","StepEasing"],"Steps"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Temporal","StepEasing"],"StepPosition"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[114,10],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Temporal/Easing.purs","start":[114,3]},"title":"Steps"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Temporal","SpringConfig"],"SpringConfig"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[115,11],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Temporal/Easing.purs","start":[115,3]},"title":"Spring"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Sch